  "texts": [
    "Deep Learning has been employed in several contexts to analyse macrofossils.",
    "Classification of vertebrate specimens is a well-explored task (refer to",
    "Elsayed et al. (2023) present a DL framework for classifying the teeth of vertebrate fossils, specifically sharks, elephants, hyrax, and Afradapis (an extinct primate).",
    "They employed ResNet50, VGG16, and other CNN models on 2D images to accurately identify and classify fossilized teeth, even in cases where the tooth is incomplete or partially damaged.",
    "However, the models' inherent restriction to differentiate between the teeth of only four vertebrate clades is a limitation, and its broader applicability across more vertebrate groups has yet to be tested."
  ],
